---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout 
	title="Crowd-Validation Commerce Disclosure - PRiority"
	description="Commercial disclosure for PRiority crowd-validation campaign - validating demand before building."
>
	<div class="relative overflow-hidden">
		<!-- Animated background -->
		<div class="fixed inset-0 mesh-gradient opacity-30 z-[-20]"></div>
		<div class="fixed inset-0 z-[-15]">
			<div class="absolute -top-40 -right-40 w-80 h-80 bg-purple-500 rounded-full mix-blend-multiply filter blur-3xl opacity-10 animate-float"></div>
			<div class="absolute -bottom-40 -left-40 w-80 h-80 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mix-blend-multiply filter blur-3xl opacity-10 animate-float" style="animation-delay: 2s;"></div>
		</div>
		
		<!-- Navigation -->
		<nav class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-[100] px-6 py-4 lg:px-12 bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-gray-800/50">
			<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between">
				<div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
					<a href="/PRiority/">
						<img src="/PRiority/logo.png" alt="PRiority Logo" class="h-12 w-auto object-contain" />
					</a>
				</div>
				<div class="flex items-center space-x-6">
					<a href="/PRiority/" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-all duration-200 font-medium">‚Üê Back to Home</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</nav>

		<main class="relative z-20 pt-20 px-6 py-20 lg:px-12">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<!-- Important Notice Banner -->
				<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500/20 to-blue-500/20 border border-purple-500/30 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
					<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
						<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-400 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
						</svg>
						<div>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Important: This is a Dream Support Platform</h2>
							<p class="text-gray-300">
								This is <strong class="text-white">NOT traditional crowdfunding</strong>. This is a platform for 
								<strong class="text-white">supporting dreams and validating ideas</strong>. Your contribution says 
								"I want this to exist in the world" and supports the exploration of whether it's possible.
								For information about the envisioned PRiority platform services, 
								see our <a href="/PRiority/platform-disclosure" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Platform Commerce Disclosure</a>.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card p-8 lg:p-12">
					<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 gradient-text">Crowd-Validation Campaign Commerce Disclosure</h1>
					
					<div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300">
						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Campaign Organizer</h2>
							<p><strong>Legal Name:</strong> G Productions, LLM</p>
							<p><strong>Name:</strong> G√ºnther Brunner</p>
							<p><strong>Role:</strong> Creator of PRiority Platform</p>
							<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:priority@g-productions.studio" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">priority@g-productions.studio</a></p>
							<p><strong>Phone:</strong> We will disclose without delay if requested</p>
							<p><strong>Address:</strong> We will disclose without delay if requested</p>
							<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://gunta.github.io/PRiority" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">https://gunta.github.io/PRiority</a></p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">What is Dream Support & Validation?</h2>
							<p class="mb-4">This is a new model for supporting ideas you want to see in the world:</p>
							
							<div class="bg-purple-500/10 border border-purple-500/30 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
								<p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">üí≠ What Your Support Means:</p>
								<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
									<li><strong>"I believe in this vision"</strong> - You want PRiority to exist</li>
									<li><strong>"I support you personally"</strong> - You back the creator's journey</li>
									<li><strong>"This problem matters"</strong> - You validate the need</li>
									<li><strong>"Count me in"</strong> - You're part of the story</li>
									<li><strong>"Make it happen"</strong> - You fuel the exploration</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							
							<p><strong>Your support helps me:</strong></p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
								<li>Know that people care about solving open source sustainability</li>
								<li>Understand which aspects resonate most</li>
								<li>Dedicate time to explore and develop the concept</li>
								<li>Build a community of believers before building the product</li>
								<li>Validate that this dream is worth pursuing</li>
							</ul>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Nature of Transaction</h2>
							<div class="bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/30 rounded-lg p-4">
								<p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">‚ö†Ô∏è THIS IS PURE SUPPORT, NOT A PURCHASE</p>
								<p class="mb-3">
									Your payment is <strong class="text-white">support for an idea</strong> and the work to explore it. 
									This is <strong class="text-white">NOT</strong>:
								</p>
								<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
									<li>A pre-order for software</li>
									<li>A guarantee that PRiority will be built</li>
									<li>A promise of specific features or timelines</li>
									<li>An investment with equity or ownership rights</li>
									<li>A refundable contribution</li>
								</ul>
								<p class="mt-3">
									<strong class="text-blue-400">You're supporting the dream, the exploration, and the validation process itself.</strong>
								</p>
							</div>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Support Tiers & Thank-You Rewards</h2>
							<p class="mb-4">Each tier represents a different level of belief in the vision. Rewards are <strong class="text-white">thank-you gifts, not guaranteed deliverables</strong>:</p>
							
							<div class="space-y-4">
								<div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4">
									<h3 class="font-bold text-blue-400">$5 - Coffee Supporter</h3>
									<p>Thank you mention in README</p>
								</div>
								
								<div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4">
									<h3 class="font-bold text-purple-400">$20 - Pizza Patron</h3>
									<p>Early access to beta + README mention</p>
								</div>
								
								<div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4">
									<h3 class="font-bold text-green-400">$50 - True Believer</h3>
									<p>Priority support + Beta access + 3 months Pro tier</p>
								</div>
								
								<div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4">
									<h3 class="font-bold text-yellow-400">$100 - MVP Backer</h3>
									<p>6 months Pro tier + Priority support + Input on features</p>
								</div>
								
								<div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4">
									<h3 class="font-bold text-orange-400">$500 - Ship It Captain</h3>
									<p>1 year Pro tier + Direct line to founder + Feature prioritization input</p>
								</div>
								
								<div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4">
									<h3 class="font-bold text-red-400">$1000 - Scale Builder</h3>
									<p>Lifetime Pro access + Monthly calls + Advisory role opportunity</p>
								</div>
								
								<div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4">
									<h3 class="font-bold text-pink-400">$5000 - Unicorn Maker</h3>
									<p>Lifetime Enterprise tier + Strategic advisor role + Revenue share consideration</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="bg-purple-500/10 border border-purple-500/30 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
								<p class="text-sm">
									<strong class="text-purple-400">üíú About Rewards:</strong> These are aspirational thank-you gifts. If PRiority gets built, 
									you'll receive these as our way of saying thanks. If not, you still supported something meaningful - 
									the exploration of a solution to open source sustainability.
								</p>
							</div>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Payment Processing</h2>
							<p><strong>Payment Processor:</strong> Stripe, Inc.</p>
							<p><strong>Additional fees:</strong> ¬•0</p>
							<p><strong>Sales Price (Including Consumption Tax):</strong> Amounts listed on each product page</p>
							<p><strong>Accepted Payment Methods:</strong></p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
								<li>Credit Cards (Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Discover)</li>
								<li>Debit Cards</li>
								<li>Digital Wallets (Apple Pay, Google Pay, where available)</li>
							</ul>
							<p class="mt-2">All payments are processed immediately upon confirmation.</p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Refund Policy</h2>
							<div class="bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/30 rounded-lg p-4">
								<p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">üì¢ NO REFUNDS - THIS IS PURE SUPPORT</p>
								<p>
									All contributions are <strong class="text-white">final and non-refundable</strong>. 
									By contributing, you understand and accept that:
								</p>
								<ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
									<li>You're supporting an idea and vision, not buying a product</li>
									<li>The work of validation and exploration has value regardless of outcome</li>
									<li>Your contribution supports the time, effort, and resources already invested</li>
									<li>This may lead to building PRiority, or it may not</li>
									<li>The journey of validation is part of what you're supporting</li>
								</ul>
								
								<p class="mt-4 text-white">
									<strong>Think of it like:</strong> Supporting an artist to explore a concept, backing a researcher's 
									investigation, or funding an inventor's experiments. The exploration itself has value.
								</p>
							</div>
							
							<div class="bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
								<p class="text-sm">
									<strong>üíô Your Trust Matters:</strong> While there are no refunds, I'm committed to being 
									completely transparent about the validation process, findings, and decisions. You'll know exactly 
									what your support accomplished.
								</p>
							</div>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">The Validation Journey</h2>
							<p><strong>What Happens Next:</strong></p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
								<li><strong>Validation Period:</strong> January - March 2025</li>
								<li><strong>Community Building:</strong> Connect supporters and gather feedback</li>
								<li><strong>Market Research:</strong> Deep dive into the problem space</li>
								<li><strong>Decision Point:</strong> Evaluate if and how to proceed</li>
								<li><strong>Transparent Updates:</strong> Regular communication throughout</li>
							</ul>
							
							<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500/10 to-purple-500/10 border border-purple-500/30 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
								<p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">üåü What Success Looks Like:</p>
								<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm">
									<li>A community of people who believe in the vision</li>
									<li>Clear understanding of the real problem to solve</li>
									<li>Validation that this matters to enough people</li>
									<li>Insights that shape the eventual solution</li>
									<li>Momentum to move forward (or wisdom to pivot)</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							
							<p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-400">
								* The validation process itself creates value - understanding, community, and clarity - regardless of the final decision.
							</p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Risks & Challenges</h2>
							<p>As with any crowd-validation campaign, there are risks involved:</p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
								<li>Development delays due to technical complexity</li>
								<li>Changes in third-party API availability or pricing</li>
								<li>Regulatory or compliance requirements</li>
								<li>Market conditions affecting launch timing</li>
							</ul>
							<p class="mt-4">
								We are committed to transparent communication and will provide regular updates on progress and any challenges encountered.
							</p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Tax Considerations</h2>
							<p>
								Crowd-validation contributions may not be tax-deductible. Contributors are responsible for 
								understanding and complying with their local tax obligations. We recommend consulting 
								with a tax professional if you have questions about the tax treatment of your contribution.
							</p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Communication & Updates</h2>
							<p>Campaign updates will be provided through:</p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
								<li>Email updates to contributors</li>
								<li>GitHub repository updates</li>
								<li>Twitter/X (@gunta85)</li>
								<li>Project website</li>
							</ul>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Intellectual Property</h2>
							<p>
								PRiority will be released as open source software. Contributors do not receive 
								ownership rights or equity in the project. Rewards are limited to those explicitly 
								described in the contribution tiers.
							</p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Privacy & Data Protection</h2>
							<p>
								Contributor information is collected solely for campaign administration and reward 
								fulfillment. We do not sell or share personal information with third parties except 
								as necessary for payment processing (Stripe) and reward delivery.
							</p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Governing Law</h2>
							<p>
								This crowd-validation campaign and all related matters are governed by the laws of the United States and Japan. 
								Any disputes will be resolved through appropriate legal channels in the United States or Japan, as applicable.
							</p>
						</section>

						<section>
							<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Contact Information</h2>
							<p>For questions about the crowd-validation campaign:</p>
							<p class="mt-2">
								<strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/gunta" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline" target="_blank">@gunta</a><br>
								<strong>Twitter/X:</strong> <a href="https://x.com/gunta85" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline" target="_blank">@gunta85</a>
							</p>
						</section>

						<section class="pt-8 border-t border-gray-700">
							<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
								<strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2025<br>
								<strong>Document Type:</strong> Crowd-Validation Campaign Disclosure<br>
								<strong>Status:</strong> Active Campaign
							</p>
						</section>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
	</div>
</Layout>

